    • Field Detail

      • LIMIT

        static final String LIMIT
        The maximum number of objects to return..
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • OFFSET

        static final String OFFSET
        The index of the first playlist to return. Default: 0 (the first object). Use with limit to get the next set of objects (albums, playlists, etc).
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ALBUM_TYPE

        static final String ALBUM_TYPE
        A comma-separated list of keywords that will be used to filter the response. Valid values are: album, single, appears_on, compilation
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • MARKET

        static final String MARKET
        The country: an ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code. Limit the response to one particular geographical market. Synonym to COUNTRY
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • COUNTRY

        static final String COUNTRY
        Same as MARKET
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • LOCALE

        static final String LOCALE
        The desired language, consisting of a lowercase ISO 639 language code * and an uppercase ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code, joined by an underscore. For example: es_MX, meaning "Spanish (Mexico)".
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
